<div class="container familyActivity">
<h2  class="page-title13">Exciting Travel Activities</h2>
  <p class="text01">Supporting adoptee identity means much more than simply providing opportunities to learn about birth country culture. To give you a unique, life-changing experience, Lead to China offers a different set of special activities for the adoptive family, such as watching a kungfu performance, flying kites, riding bicycle on the Ancient City Wall, making dumplings with a local family and so on. All the below activities can be tailored to your private family tour. Come with us to experience China differently now!</p>
 <div class="row">
    <div class="activity-block  col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Make Dumplings</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-1.jpg" class="img-responsive"   />
      <p>Your guide will escort you to a local family, we will prepare the ingredients and you will learn how to make dumpling or wonton with them. Then you can enjoy your own fruit for lunch with the family. </p>
    </div>
    <div class="activity-block  col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Visit a Local School</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-2.jpg" class="img-responsive"  />
      <p>Visiting a Primary or Junior High School, the activities are: visiting the school, having a class with the local students, the children can have some interaction with each other and communicate about the hobbies and interests, etc </p>
    </div>

    <div class="activity-block  col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Countryside Biking</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-3.jpg" class="img-responsive"  />
      <p>Rent bicycle in West Street, cycle along Yulong River, pass through rice paddies, vegetable fields, and an orchard, and take photos with water buffalos. Your family will have fun in this beautiful area. </p>
    </div>
    <div class="activity-block  col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Chinese Calligraphy</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-5.jpg" class="img-responsive"  />
      <p>First there'll be a general introdution about Four Treasures of the Study in China: the Brush, Ink, Paper and Ink Stone. Then you will learn how to write Chinese characters and write your name in Chinese!</p>
    </div>
    
    

    
    <div class="activity-block  col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Make and Fly Kite</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-11.jpg"  class="img-responsive" />
      <p>We will prepare all the meterials, the teacher will first introduce the procedure,and then begin to make the skeleton and papering. The teacher will help with the children all the process. Then we will find a stadium/square for you to fly the kite.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="activity-block col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Paint Panda T-shirts</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-6.jpg" class="img-responsive"  />
      <p>In Chengdu, you can learn Panda Painting. Firstly we will invite a professional artist to teach you how to draw a panda in a teahouse. After you are familiar with the painting, you can draw a panda in a blank T-shirt. After the course, you will keep your own made panda T-shirt and wear it home. It'll be a perfect souvenir. </p>
    </div>

    <div class="activity-block col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Makeup for the Sichuan Opera</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-7.jpg" class="img-responsive"  />
      <p>After watching the Sichuan Opera, you will have a chance to be maked up as the performer. It will be a fun way to experience the local culture.</p>
    </div>
     <div class="activity-block  col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Watch an Acrobatic Show </span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-12.jpg" class="img-responsive"  />
      <p>You can watch this performance in Shanghai or Beijing. It costs about 60 mins, contains several stunts: Bicycle acrobatics,Circles jumping,Contortion.. . You will be amazed by these talented artists.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="activity-block col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Learn to Cook Chinese Dishes </span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-9.jpg" class="img-responsive"  />
      <p>You can do this activity in Yangshuo, Guilin. In the morning, you will be taken to a local food market to buy vegetables, and then back to the kitchen, wash and chop dishes, learn to cook. You will learn all the procedure of cooking Chinese cuisine and have fun.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="activity-block col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Visit a Local Family</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-4.jpg"  class="img-responsive" />
      <p>The local family visting can be arranged in Beijing or Xian. We especially have chosen typical local families to host this activity in which you can see the true living standard of Chinese people. You can  taste the true home cooked dishes in the home of the family that you visit, you can also learn to cook chinese food if you want.</p>
    </div>

  	
    <div class="activity-block  col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Watch a Kungfu Show</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-10.jpg"  class="img-responsive" />
      <p>The Legend of Kung Fu Show--a must-see production in Beijing for tourists and Kung Fu lovers, is a mix of traditional martial arts and modern theatre. Presenting stunning Kung Fu skills, exquisite ballet and music, this beautiful story in no doubt has become the most loved Kung Fu show in China.
The story tells of about a young boy who dreams of becoming a Kung Fu master and attain enlightenment. He takes the path of a monk in which he must face many obstacles both from this world and his own mind to overcome his fears and to become a true master of Kung Fu.
The show made its first appearance on the Beijing stage in July 15th 2004. Ever since it has received numerous awards and become a world class spectacle known around the world. 
</p>
    </div>
    <div class="activity-block col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12"> <span class="title01">Visit the Giant Panda</span> <img src="/images/familyActivity-8.jpg" class="img-responsive"  />
      <p>Visit the home of giant pandas at Panda Breeding and Research Center, in the outskirts of Chengdu. Visit the nursery to see the highly successful breeding program, among the bamboo groves and shady walkways, and to view the pandas at rest or play. There is a panda museum where you can learn some information about giant pandas.<br />
        In order to protect the giant pandas from becoming infected with the canine distemper virus, all the panda bases stopped public interaction with the pandas from January, 2015. Dujiangyan Panda Base has reopened the volunteer program as well as the program to take photos next to a panda since March, 2015. If you would like to join the Panda Volunteer Program or take photos with a panda next to you, we are happy to arrange a day tour to Dujiangyan Panda Valley for you. </p>
    </div>    
</div>
</div>